#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:6
#: 07b71dd085ac4b9397d90241a8a3c937
msgid "Software that is too complicated to use, is often unused. Because we want as many people as possible to benefit from its unique security properties, the usability and user experience of Qubes OS is an utmost priority!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:11
#: f91a488007664562981fd4ebe8767627
msgid "We ask anyone developing for Qubes OS to please read through this guide to better understand the user experience we strive to achieve. We also ask them to review :doc:`our visual style guide </developer/general/visual-style-guide>` for other design related information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:21
#: eafe5b72434b4631b1b1c5bf590cdc24
msgid "Easy To Use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:24
#: 74e5a2bc82844b2c81273f4e9f6ce05a
msgid "An ideal user experience is friendly, and it beckons a new user to explore the interface. In this process, they can naturally discover how to use the software. Below are some guidelines that will help you design a user interface that accomplishes this goal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:30
#: 118b5e0451494104b0a4e907f9bf37da
msgid "Interfaces Should Not"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:33
#: 9d6b5bbcbeec4fb7861ddbcc312976a0
msgid "Require extensive configuration before a user can *begin* doing things"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:36
#: ca720c280912472da50bc66cae7de619
msgid "Make it possible to break provided features or actions in unrecoverable ways"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:39
#: f3436c2d2c8b43fbb9b0b481fac448cc
msgid "Perform actions which compromise security and data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:41
#: 57f9c4738a5646e6856327a055608e7c
msgid "Overwhelm the user with too much information and cognitive load"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:45
#: 176316cddcfb4c48818f378c3c9736c4
msgid "Perhaps the most common cause of mistakes is complexity. If there is a configuration setting that will significantly affect the user’s experience, choose a safe and smart default then tuck this setting in an ``Advanced Settings`` panel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:51
#: 6efb0e9b913f41028baedd92b3b48d10
msgid "Interfaces Should"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:54
#: 2f7b54ff8cfd4a1b92b16d2494c50801
msgid "Make it easy to discover features and available actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:56
#: c4e21ff82e2c499c85eda6c7bb3d731b
msgid "Provide some understanding of what discovered features do"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:58
#: 4dd2fabe5c394a95ae3b8c37aef1ddf1
msgid "Offer the ability to easily undo mistakes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:60
#: 0ae490b3409347aa917baf78fee17c3a
msgid "Choose intelligent defaults for settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:64
#: e877210608e74d1dbe474b3d78a8911c
msgid "In making software easy to use, it is crucial to be mindful of `cognitive load <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cognitive_load>`__ which dictates that *“humans are generally able to hold only seven +/- two units of information in short-term memory.”* Making sure your interfaces don’t pass this short-term memory limit is perhaps the most important factor in helping a user feel comfortable instead of overwhelmed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:75
#: 524e2d867e664ba888321de706ac051f
msgid "Easy to Understand"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:78
#: 19206a71dad14cc6be66769374af5bd7
msgid "There will always be the need to communicate things to users. In these cases, an interface should aim to make this information easy to understand. The following are simple guides to help achieve this - none of these are absolute maxims!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:84
#: 4ee8f127bef34cd7803cef406207474a
msgid "Avoid Acronyms"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:87
#: 31076c4ada9c4ba9aa1695b1481f7625
msgid "Acronyms are compact and make good names for command line tools. They do not make graphical user interfaces more intuitive for non-technical users. Until one learns an acronym’s meaning, it is gibberish. Avoid acronyms in your interfaces whenever possible!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:92
#: 9da2b9ee0b5a4e8b94f42ee727ad70bd
msgid "``DVM`` - Disposable Virtual Machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:94
#: 4e598e7de27645fca91934d970e6a084
msgid "``GUID`` - Global Unique Identifier"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:96
#: be6f35a6f48e4a4284b5cd2c65ad0960
msgid "``PID`` - Process Identification Number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:98
#: 7dcd7dae930f4f298f1c807c6b64db0f
msgid "``NetVM`` - Networking Virtual Machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:102
#: 521d5de4a1684e3aa74a8da8ccdd519e
msgid "Despite this rule, some acronyms like ``USB`` are widely used and understood due to being in common use for over a decade. It is good to use these acronyms when the full words like ``Universal Serial Bus`` are more likely to confuse users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:108
#: 2c033339b0934bf18e67c8d7043403be
msgid "Use Simple Words"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:111
#: 0df4187571aa45ecbca4565e7875f7c0
msgid "Use the minimum amount of words needed to be descriptive, but also informative. Go with common words that are as widely understood. Sometimes, inventing a word such as ``Qube`` to describe a ``virtual machine`` makes the life of the user much easier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:116
#: ff98e64c5dfc4b9eb7083941461d7187
msgid "Use ``Disposable Qube`` instead of ``DVM`` or ``Disposable Virtual Machine``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:119
#: f357b2f85cb948d8b20d192057e9bb39
msgid "Use ``interface`` instead of ``GUI`` or ``Graphical User Interface``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:121
#: ef83dc285cae4310904f1b0398d988d0
msgid "Use ``application number`` instead of ``PID`` or ``Process Identification Number``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:124
#: 37ec6761977742728a39f8216763415c
msgid "Use ``Networking`` or ``Networking Qube`` instead of ``NetVM`` given context"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:134
#: d09c14bbdb7c4e10a1be213bd9f3f909
msgid "Avoid Technical Words"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:137
#: 1d3c5b039f144fa0b706b55b7055d20f
msgid "Technical words are usually more accurate, but they often *only* make sense to technical users and are confusing and unhelpful to non-technical users. Examples of technical words that might show up in Qubes OS are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:142
#: aad6a05c69ce416c8011ad34cc0fa5d2
msgid "``root.img``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:144
#: efed6e22c5e644f8b33e170a5cf8d227
msgid "``savefile``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:146
#: 5349c0d5bb2b4fd19dcb1ffd4f49bcd0
msgid "``qrexec-daemon``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:150
#: 03e226b206cb41acb00573101f5b93be
msgid "These are all terms that have at some point showed up in users’ notification messages. Each term is very specific, but requires the user to understand virtualization to interpret."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:155
#: 97d9ec86924945bd8a033510b20c2de2
msgid "Use Common Concepts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:158
#: 8111232104ae46cc8008a7ff76b38249
msgid "Large amounts of the global population have been using computers for one or two decades and have formed some mental models of how things work. Leveraging these mental models are a huge gain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:162
#: 8663ffd8decf43a3bc14ce6f0d0526a4
msgid "Use ``disk space`` instead of ``root.img``, since while not quite accurate, it makes contextual sense"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:165
#: 075da63166b84ae590f60a26b6ca274d
msgid "Use ``saving`` instead of ``savefile`` as the former is the action trying to be completed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:168
#: 0a147312d9ae4dff939e696de3c07b6e
msgid "Use ``Qubes`` instead of ``qrexec-daemon`` as it gives better context on what is happening"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:173
#: 92fef95f9fc2425183c3f3932c955b1f
msgid "These words are more abstract and user relevant- they help a user understand what is happening based on already known concepts (disk space) or start to form a mental model of something new (Qubes)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:182
#: 0c92ba9773744ad9b8a5f23e97e0ada7
msgid "Avoid Inconsistencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:185
#: 2511080c025842c98535fef5ee4d6e2b
msgid "It is easy to start abbreviating (or making acronyms) of long terms like ``Disposable Virtual Machine`` depending on where the term shows up in an interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:189
#: 5071076f8d484343a85b58654e23c024
msgid "``DVM``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:191
#: 6cb46ac04fec4e4fbdc5ef9ca6d8fc85
msgid "``DispVM``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:193
#: 4567ddef4bee489e8a6cb62dd3562d0d
msgid "``DisposableVM``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:197
#: 62a86a6e80254aa18e70aab247134d7e
msgid "This variation in terms can cause new users to question or second guess what the three different variations mean, which can lead to inaction or mistakes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:202
#: f02c3b5d8aa04f928c8cdff83b7f292c
msgid "Make Things Consistent"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:205
#: 0b64a7de6e1a42c3a3bf926d0ce3beb6
msgid "Always strive to keep things consistent in the interfaces as well as documentation and other materials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:208
#: 379e27d7647041e4ac05a71be4182070
msgid "Use ``Disposable Qube`` at all times as it meets other criteria as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:213
#: 10b26cd596544817ae9904531faec5c8
msgid "By using the same term throughout an interface, a user can create a mental model and relationship with that term allowing them to feel empowered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:222
#: 78d44bb7d273472c95df2407727f1417
msgid "Avoid Duplicate Words"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:225
#: 9ff2b2845434420088103d876b1dc4d3
msgid "It is easy to add words like ``Domain`` before items in a list or menu in an attempt to be descriptive, such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:237
#: 846e05ff5e7e4d00a9a32764464513ca
msgid "The repeated use of the word ``Domain`` requires a user to read it for each item in the list, which makes extra work for the eye in parsing out the relevant word like ``work, banking, or personal``. This also affects horizontal space on fixed width lines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:243
#: cce003b8e53849e89f809fa7b78ea2f5
msgid "Create Groups & Categories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:246
#: 61c15f76bf2c4791820493b8521e6888
msgid "It is more efficient to group things under headings instead as this allows the eye to easily scan the uniqueness of the items. (As per our previous example:)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:264
#: dd9c361a22244e84a1bced0b02126091
msgid "Easy To Complete"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer/general/usability-ux.rst:267
#: 81955a96f9b6446fb4070255b8e6860c
msgid "Lastly, expected (and unexpected) situations often require user actions or input. Make resolving these occurences as easy as possible to complete the action."
msgstr ""

